# Hospital Bed Allocation System — Turing Machine Simulation

Automata Theory class project: a Turing Machine model of a hospital bed
allocation engine, implemented in C++.

## Overview

This program models bed allocation as a Turing Machine that reads a
patient's ID and severity from a tape, scans eligible wards for a free
bed, and **writes** the allocated ward and bed number back onto the
tape before halting (accept) or rejecting (queue) the patient.

## Why a Turing Machine (not a DFA/NFA)

| Capability | DFA / NFA | This TM |
|---|---|---|
| Write to tape | No | Yes — writes ward + bed number |
| Move head left | No (right only) | Yes — retries previous ward |
| Unbounded memory | No | Yes — tape grows with allocation |

## States

| State | Description |
|---|---|
| `READ_PATIENT` (q0) | Reads patient ID from tape |
| `CHECK_SEVERITY` (q1) | Reads severity level |
| `SCAN_WARD` (q2) | Scans eligible wards for a free bed |
| `MATCH_FOUND` (q3) | A ward with a free bed was found |
| `NO_MATCH` (q4) | Ward full — retry next ward or reject |
| `ALLOCATE` (q5) | Writes ward + bed number to tape |
| `UPDATE_TAPE` (q6) | Finalizes the tape |
| `HALT` (q7) | Accept (allocated) or reject (queued) |

## Build & Run

```bash
g++ -std=c++17 -o hospital_tm HospitalBedTM.cpp
./hospital_tm
```

## Files

- `HospitalBedTM.cpp` — full C++ source (single file)
- `report/` — class report with theory mapping and code screenshots

## Sample Output

```
ADMITTING PATIENT: Alice M. (P001)
Severity: CRITICAL | Ward Preference: ICU
...
RESULT: ALLOCATED -> Ward = ICU, Bed = 1
```

